'''Santiago Tomás Giménez Zolotarchuk'''<ref name="football-italia.net">https://football-italia.net/why-milan-players-will-wear-different-surnames/</ref> ({{IPA|es|sanˈtjaɣo toˈmas xiˈmenes}}; born 18 April 2001) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]]. Born in Argentina, he represents the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

Giménez started his career with [[Liga MX]] club [[Cruz Azul]] for four seasons winning various competitions, among them the [[2020–21 Liga MX season#Torneo Guardianes 2021|league title]] and the [[Apertura 2018 Copa MX|Copa MX]], before a transfer to [[Feyenoord]] in July 2022. His time in the Netherlands saw him win the [[Eredivisie]], the [[KNVB Cup]] and [[Johan Cruyff Shield]]. He joined AC Milan in 2025 for €37 million.

Giménez made his full international debut for Mexico in 2021; he represented the country at the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], scoring the winning goal in the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup final|final]], and would win the tournament for a second time in [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2025]]. He also won the [[2025 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2025]] edition of the [[CONCACAF Nations League]], and finished as runner-up in [[2024 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2024]].

==Club career==
===Cruz Azul===
On 2 August 2017, Giménez made his professional debut with [[Cruz Azul]] in a [[Apertura 2017 Copa MX|Copa MX]] group stage match against [[Tigres UANL]] in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 August 2017 |title=Cruz Azul: Santiago Giménez, el hijo del Chaco, debuta en un juego oficial |trans-title=Cruz Azul: Santiago Giménez, the son of Chaco, makes his debut in an official match. |url=https://www.marca.com/claro-mx/futbol/copa-mx/2017/08/03/5982b140e5fdea1a7f8b462e.html |website=MARCA Claro México}}</ref> Two years later, on 28 August 2019, he made his [[Liga MX]] debut against [[Club Tijuana|Tijuana]] in a 3–2 loss.<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 August 2019 |title=Debut de Santiago Giménez ⋆ Cruz Azul Fútbol Club |trans-title=Debut of Santiago Giménez ⋆ Cruz Azul Football Club |url=https://www.cruzazulfc.com.mx/debut-de-santiago-gimenez/ |work=Cruz Azul Fútbol Club |access-date=14 September 2020 |archive-date=4 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201004202858/https://www.cruzazulfc.com.mx/debut-de-santiago-gimenez/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> He would score his first goal with the club on 2 February 2020, in a league match against [[Deportivo Toluca F.C.|Toluca]] in a 3–3 tie, scoring within the first two minutes of the match.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ante Toluca y con Cruz Azul, primer gol de Santiago Giménez en Primera División |trans-title=Against Toluca, Santiago Giménez scores his first goal in First Division. |url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/liga-mx/ante-toluca-primer-gol-de-santiago-gimenez-en-primera-division |access-date=5 May 2025 |website=www.tudn.com |date=2 February 2020 |language=es}}</ref>

In May 2021, Cruz Azul won its ninth league championship, ending a 23-year drought of league titles.<ref name="Guardianes">{{Cite web |last=Serrano |first=Rodrigo |date=1 June 2021 |title=Cruz Azul beat Santos to end their 24-year championship drought |url=https://en.as.com/en/2021/05/31/soccer/1622416584_273330.html |access-date=22 May 2024 |website=Diario AS |language=en-us}}</ref>

In August, scoring in four separate league matches, Giménez was named Liga MX Player of the Month.<ref name="August">{{cite web |title=Cruz Azul: Santiago Giménez es elegido como el jugador del mes de agosto en la Liga MX |work=Soy Fútbol |trans-title=Cruz Azul: Santiago Giménez is chosen as the Player of the Month for August in Liga MX. |url=https://www.soyfutbol.com/ligas/Cruz-Azul-Santiago-Gimenez-es-elegido-como-el-jugador-del-mes-de-agosto-en-la-Liga-MX-20210916-0055.html}}</ref> He won the award again the subsequent month.<ref name="September">{{cite web |date=19 October 2021 |title=FIFA 22 reconoció a Santiago Giménez como uno de los mejores jugadores |trans-title=FIFA 22 recognized Santiago Giménez as one of the best players. |url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/videojuegos/ea/santiago-gimenez-reconocido-ea-sports-fifa-22-jugador-del-mes}}</ref> On 26 June 2022, at the [[Supercopa de la Liga MX]] against [[Atlas F.C.|Atlas]], he scored in the match, ending at 2–2 and going into penalties, where he successfully converted his shot as his team won the cup.<ref name="Supercopa">{{Cite web |title=Campeón de Campeones: Cruz Azul derrota al Atlas en penales y gana la Supercopa MX |trans-title=Campeón de Campeones: Cruz Azul defeats Atlas in a penalty shootout and wins the Supercopa MX. |url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/liga-mx/campeon-de-campeones-cruz-azul-derrota-atlas-penales-gana-supercopa-mx |access-date=22 May 2024 |website=www.tudn.com |date=26 June 2022 |language=es}}</ref>

===Feyenoord===

==== 2022–23: Debut season and Eredivisie champion ====
On 29 July 2022, Giménez joined [[Feyenoord]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |date=29 July 2022 |title=Feyenoord contracteert centrumspits Santiago Gimenez |trans-title=Feyenoord signs center forward Santiago Giménez. |url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/feyenoord-contracteert-centrumspits-santiago-gimenez---290722 |publisher=Feyenoord |language=nl}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for the club on 27 August, scoring the second goal in the club's 4–0 win over [[FC Emmen]] while also providing the assist for [[Jacob Rasmussen]] to score the club's third goal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/feyenoord-in-debuutgoalgala-langs-fc-emmen |title=Feyenoord in debuutgoalgala langs FC Emmen |language=nl|date=27 August 2022 |access-date=27 August 2022}}</ref> On 8 September, he made his [[UEFA Europa League]] debut against Italian club [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] in that [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League|season's edition]] in a group stage match, coming on as a substitute at the 64th minute and scoring twice in the club's 4–2 loss.<ref>{{cite web |date=9 September 2022 |title=Santiago Giménez se luce con doblete en Europa League, pero no evita la derrota del Feyenoord |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/reporte/_/juegoId/652697 |access-date=9 December 2023 |website=ESPN Deportes}}</ref> On 3 November, after coming on as a substitute, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory in the return game against Lazio in the Europa League group stage, securing Feyenoord's first-place finish in the group and directly qualifying to the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of 16]].<ref>{{cite web |date=3 November 2022 |title=Santi Giménez rompió sequía de dos meses con gol a la Lazio |trans-title=Santi Giménez broke a two-month goal drought with a goal against Lazio. |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/uefa-europa-league/nota/_/id/11176345/santi-gimenez-rompio-sequia-de-dos-meses-con-gol-a-la-lazio}}</ref>

Feyenoord went on to win the [[2022–23 Eredivisie]], with Giménez scoring 15 goals in 32 matches, including the second goal in a 3–0 win over [[Go Ahead Eagles]] to secure the league title.<ref name="2023Champions"/> Across all competitions, Giménez scored 23 goals, breaking the record for most goals scored in a debut European season by a Mexican, surpassing the 20-goal tallies of [[Javier Hernández]] and [[Luis García (footballer, born 1969)|Luis García]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/europa/nota/_/id/12013909/santiago-gimenez-mexicano-con-mas-goles-en-europa-temporada-debut|title='Chaquito', el mexicano con más goles en su temporada debut en Europa|date=7 May 2023|website=ESPNdeportes.com}}</ref>

==== 2023–24: Individual success and KNVB Cup champion ====
In August 2023, Giménez extended his contract with Feyenoord for one year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/feyenoord-houdt-gewilde-gimenez-binnenboord |title=Feyenoord houdt gewilde Giménez binnenboord |work=Voetbal International |trans-title=Feyenoord keeps wanted Giménez on board |language=nl |date=3 August 2023 |access-date=3 August 2023}}</ref>

Giménez began the [[2023–24 Feyenoord season|2023–24 season]] on 4 August in the [[2023 Johan Cruyff Shield|Johan Cruyff Shield]], playing 62 minutes as [[PSV Eindhoven]] defeated them 1–0 to win their third consecutive title.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 August 2023 |title=PSV Eindhoven win Dutch Super Cup |website=[[Reuters]] |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/psv-eindhoven-win-dutch-super-cup-2023-08-04/}}</ref> On 20 August, Giménez scored his first goal of the season in a 2–2 draw against [[Sparta Rotterdam]]. In the following games, on 27 August and 3 September, Giménez scored two [[brace (sports)|brace]]s, one in a 6–1 win against [[Almere City FC|Almere City]] and another in a 5–1 away win against [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=27 August 2023 |title=Mexican forward Santiago Giménez continues to shine at Feyenoord |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/mexican-forward-santiago-gimenez-continues-to-shine-at-feyenoord-n/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=3 September 2023 |title=FC Utrecht still without a point this season, as Feyenoord defeat them comfortably |url=https://nltimes.nl/2023/09/03/fc-utrecht-still-without-point-season-feyenoord-defeat-comfortably}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=4 September 2023 |title=Santi Jiménez doubles as Feyenoord beat Utrecht 5-1 at half-time |url=https://sparkchronicles.com/santi-jimenez-doubles-as-feyenoord-beat-utrecht-5-1-at-half-time/}}</ref> On 27 September, Giménez completed a [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] in a 4–0 away win over [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] by scoring the first and second goals on 24 September, and scoring the third on 27 September after the game was originally abandoned on the 24th.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/hattrick-hero-gimenez-we-hebben-twee-keer-van-ajax-gewonnen |title=Hattrick Hero Giménez: 'We hebben twee keer van Ajax gewonnen' |trans-title=Hattrick Hero Giménez: 'We beat Ajax twice' |language=nl |date=27 September 2023 |access-date=27 September 2023}}</ref> He won the Eredivisie [[Eredivisie Player of the Month|Player of the Month]] award for September.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Rosa |first1=Erick De la |last2=Brennan |first2=Joe |date=6 October 2023 |title=Santiago Giménez wins Eredivisie Player of the Month award for September |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/santiago-gimenez-wins-eredivisie-player-of-the-month-award-for-september-n/ |access-date=5 May 2025 |website=AS USA |language=en-us}}</ref>

In the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], Giménez was suspended for the first two group stage matches, having received a red card against [[AS Roma|Roma]] in the Europa League quarter-final second leg from the previous season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cons |first=Roddy |date=4 October 2023 |title=Why isn't Santi Giménez playing for Feyenoord against Atlético Madrid in the UEFA Champions League? |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/why-isnt-santi-gimenez-playing-for-feyenoord-against-atletico-madrid-in-the-uefa-champions-league-n/ |access-date=5 May 2025 |website=AS USA |language=en-us}}</ref> He made his Champions League debut on 25 October, scoring the first and third goal in a 3–1 home win over Lazio,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/feyenoord-op-indrukwekkende-wijze-naar-tweede-zege-in-champions-league |title=Feyenoord op indrukwekkende wijze naar tweede zege in Champions League |trans-title=Feyenoord gets second Champions League win in impressing way |date=25 October 2023 |access-date=25 October 2023}}</ref> winning the man of the match award.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2039122/ | title=History: Feyenoord 3-1 Lazio: UEFA Champions League 2023/24 Group stage }}</ref> On 25 November, he scored his second hat-trick of the season in a 4–2 [[Rotterdam derby]] win over [[Excelsior Rotterdam|Excelsior]] at the [[Stadion Woudestein]], ending his six-game goal drought.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Sergio Mancilla |last2=Paul Reidy |date=25 November 2023 |title=Santiago Giménez ends his goal drought |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/santiago-gimenez-ends-his-goal-drought-n/ |website= |publisher=as.com}}</ref> On 7 December, following Feyenoord's 3–1 win over [[FC Volendam|Volendam]], Giménez scored his 31st Eredivisie goal in a calendar year, surpassing previous record holder [[Luis Suárez]] who scored 30 goals in 2009.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Sebastián Gómez |last2=Kieran Quaile |date=7 December 2023 |title=Santiago Giménez breaks Luis Suárez's record with goal for Feyenoord |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/santi-gimenez-breaks-luis-suarezs-record-with-goal-for-feyenoord-n/ |website= |publisher=as.com}}</ref>

On 21 April 2024, he assisted [[Igor Paixão]] to score the winning goal in a 1–0 win over [[NEC Nijmegen]] in the [[2024 KNVB Cup final|KNVB Cup final]] to clinch a fourteenth KNVB Cup title for Feyenoord.<ref name="2024KNVBCup"/> On 5 May, he came off the bench against [[PEC Zwolle]] and scored twice as well as an assist in a 5–0 win, putting an end to his seven-game goal drought.<ref>{{cite web |date=5 May 2024 |title=Santi Giménez brilla con doblete y asistencia en triunfo el Feyenoord |trans-title=Santi Giménez shines with a double and assist in Feyenoord's victory |url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/dutch-eredivisie/santi-gimenez-brilla-con-doblete-y-asistencia-en-triunfo-el-feyenoord |access-date=5 May 2024 |website=TUDN |language=es}}</ref> Due to injuries and lack of form, he missed the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web |date=10 May 2024 |title=Santi Giménez es duda con el Feyenoord para enfrentar al NEC |trans-title= Santi Giménez is a doubt with Feyenoord to face NEC |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/nota/_/id/13638534/santi-gimenez-feyenoord-duda-para-enfrentar-a-nec |access-date=10 May 2024 |website=[[ESPN Deportes]] |language=es}}</ref> In his second season with the club, Giménez made 30 league appearances and scored 23 goals (26 goals in 40 appearances across all competitions) as the team finished second in the league, trailing to PSV by seven points.

==== 2024–25: Final season in the Netherlands ====
Giménez began his [[2024–25 Feyenoord season|2024–25 campaign]] on 4 August in the [[2024 Johan Cruyff Shield|Johan Cruyff Shield]], he went on to convert two [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick goals]], notching his 50th and 51st goals for the club, as well as assisting [[Bart Nieuwkoop]]'s goal in a 4–4 draw with the three-time defending champions PSV. Following the end of [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]], Feyenoord were victorious in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]], winning 4–2 as Giménez went on to win his third trophy with the club.<ref>{{cite web|title=Feyenoord edge PSV on penalties to win season-opening Johan Cruyff Shield|url=https://www.flashscore.com.gh/news/soccer-johan-cruyff-shield-feyenoord-edge-psv-on-penalties-to-win-season-opening-johan-cruyff-shield/fNYn2yhI/|publisher=Flashscore|date=4 August 2024}}</ref> On 22 September, Giménez was substituted during the first half of a league match against [[NAC Breda]] after sustaining an upper thigh injury, which was later confirmed two days later, keeping him out of action for three months.<ref>{{cite web|title=Medical update Santiago Giménez|url=https://www.feyenoord.com/en/news/medical-update-santiago-gimenez-240924|publisher=Feyenoord|date=24 September 2024}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=26 November 2024 |title=Santiago Giménez marca en el empate de locura entre Feyenoord y City |trans-title=Santiago Giménez scores in the crazy draw between Feyenoord and City. |url=https://www.eldictamen.mx/santiago-gimenez-gol-empate-feyenoord-city-2024/ |access-date=27 November 2024 |website=eldictamen.com |language=es}}</ref> After just two months out injured, he returned on 26 November in a Champions League match against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]; with Feyenoord 3–0 down, Giménez scored his team's second goal as they fought back to a 3–3 draw away from home.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=26 November 2024 |title=Manchester City blow three-goal lead as Feyenoord produce stunning fightback |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/nov/26/manchester-city-feyenoord-champions-league-match-report |access-date=27 November 2024 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 14 December, he scored his third hat-trick with the club in a 5–2 home victory over [[Heracles Almelo]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Feyenoord past Heracles thanks to hattrick Gimenez |url=https://www.feyenoord.com/en/news/feyenoord-past-heracles-thanks-to-hattrick-gimenez-141224 |access-date=5 May 2025 |website=www.feyenoord.com |language=en}}</ref> On 12 January 2025, he scored a penalty in a 2–1 loss to Utrecht, becoming Mexico's all-time top scorer in the Eredivisie with 45 goals, surpassing the previous record held by [[Hirving Lozano]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.footboom1.com/en/news/football/2290276-with-45-goals-santiago-gimenez-surpasses-chucky-s-record-in-the-netherlands |title=With 45 Goals, Santiago Giménez Surpasses Chucky's Record in the Netherlands |publisher=footboom1.com |date=13 January 2025 }}</ref>

===AC Milan===
On 3 February 2025, Giménez signed a four-and-a-half-year contract with [[Serie A]] club [[AC Milan]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2025-02-03/official-statement-santiago-gimenez |title=Official Statement: Santiago Gimenez |publisher=AC Milan |date=3 February 2025 }}</ref> for a reported transfer fee of €32 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/serie-a/articles/ac-milan-complete-32m-gimenez-deal-on-deadline-day-2025-02-03 |title=AC Milan complete €32m Gimenez deal on deadline day |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=3 February 2025 }}</ref> Two days later, he made his debut, providing an assist to [[João Félix]] in a 3–1 victory over [[AS Roma|Roma]] in the [[2024–25 Coppa Italia|Coppa Italia]] quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.soyfutbol.com/en/news/Santiago-Gimenez-Makes-a-Splash-with-an-Assist-in-AC-Milan-vs-Roma-Cup-Clash-20250205-0029.html |title=Santiago Giménez Makes a Splash with an Assist in AC Milan vs Roma Cup Clash |publisher=Soy Fútbol |date=5 February 2025 }}</ref> On 8 February, he scored his first goal on his Serie A debut which ended in a 2–0 away win over [[Empoli FC|Empoli]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/serie-a/articles-video/santi-gim%C3%A9nez-shines-in-serie-a-debut-with-goal-and-milan-victory-2025-02-08 |title=Santi Giménez Shines in Serie A Debut with Goal and Milan Victory |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=8 February 2025 }}</ref> On 18 February, he scored his first Champions League goal for Milan in the opening minute of a 1–1 draw against his former club Feyenoord in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|knockout phase play-offs]]; however, Milan were eliminated with a 2–1 aggregate defeat.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2044484/ |title=Milan 1–1 Feyenoord |publisher=UEFA |date=18 February 2025 }}</ref> That was also his sixth goal in that season's Champions League competition, breaking the previous record of most goals scored by a Mexican in a single Champions League season, five goals held by [[Hugo Sánchez]] and Javier Hernández.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/santiago-gimenez-sets-new-champions-league-record-despite-round-of-16-exit|title=Santiago Gimenez Sets New Champions League Record|date=18 February 2025|website=SI}}</ref> On 9 May, after coming on as a substitute during the second half, Giménez scored a brace against [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] helping his team achieve a 3–1 home win.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-my/football/serie-a/articles/milan-3-1-bologna-gimenez-brace-seals-comeback-win-in-coppa-italia-final-preview-2025-05-09|title=AC Milan 3-1 Bologna: Gimenez brace seals comeback win in Coppa Italia final preview|first=Santiago Gimenez came off the bench to score twice and fire AC Milan to a crucial win over Bologna on|last=Friday|website=beIN SPORTS}}</ref> On 28 October, Giménez sustained an ankle injury, and after spending five months on the sidelines, he made his first competitive appearance on 21 March 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2026-03-21 |title=Santiago Gimenez regresa a la actividad con AC Milan |url=https://www.espn.com.mx/futbol/italia/nota/_/id/16469974/santiago-gimenez-regreso-ac-milan-lesion-serie-a |access-date=2026-03-21 |website=ESPN.com.mx |language=es}}</ref>

==International career==
Despite having the option of representing [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], his country of birth, Giménez decided to represent [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] after becoming a naturalized Mexican citizen, stating "I feel more Mexican than Argentine,"<ref>{{cite web|title=Hoy me siento más mexicano que argentino: Santiago Giménez|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/liga-mx/santiago-gimenez-aseguro-me-siento-mas-mexicano-que-argentino|work=Medio Tiempo|date=27 September 2020}}</ref> having lived in Mexico for the majority of his life since his father moved there. He has been called up by Mexico's [[Mexico national under-15 football team|U-15]], [[Mexico national under-18 football team|U-18]], [[Mexico national under-20 football team|U-20]], and [[Mexico national under-23 football team|U-23]] teams.<ref>{{cite web|title=Santiago Giménez respondió en que Selección Nacional jugaría|url=https://naciondeportes.com/santiago-gimenez-elegiria-a-mexico-sobre-argentina/|work=Nación Deportes|date=18 May 2020|first=Andrea|last= Ibancovichi Muñoz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=J.J. Macías y Santiago Giménez, convocados con la Selección Mexicana Sub-23|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/selecciones/nota/_/id/7520771/jj-macias-santiago-gimenez-convocados-seleccion-mexicana-sub23|work=ESPN Deportes|date=1 October 2020}}</ref> He made three appearances with the [[Mexico national under-17 football team|Mexico U16]]s at the 2016 International Dream Cup.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=http://www.jfa.jp/match/u16_InternationalDreamCup_2016|title=U-16 International Dream Cup 2016 JAPAN Presented by JFA|website=JFA｜Japan Football Association}}</ref>

In September 2020, Giménez received his first senior national team call up by [[Gerardo Martino]] for a training camp.<ref>{{cite web|title=Santi rompió con la ausencia de 10 años de delanteros de Cruz Azul en la Selección|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/santiago-gimenez-cruz-azul-aporta-delantero-seleccion-10-anos|work=Medio Tiempo|date=16 September 2020}}</ref> That same month, it was reported that the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina under-20]] coach [[Fernando Batista]] was interested in calling him up.<ref>{{cite web|title=Argentina reconoce contacto con Santiago Giménez: "haremos lo posible para que esté con la Albiceleste"|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/selecciones/nota/_/id/7471633/santiago-gimenez-cruz-azul-contactos-argentina-sub-20|work=ESPN Deportes|date=22 September 2020}}</ref> On 27 October 2021, Giménez made his senior debut for Mexico in a friendly match against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/santiago-gimenez-tridente-lujo-juego-ecuador|title= Santiago Giménez será parte del tridente de lujo en el juego contra Ecuador|website=mediotiempo.com|date=27 October 2021}}</ref> On 8 December, he scored his first goal for Mexico in a friendly match against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] that ended at a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.espn.com.mx/futbol/selecciones/nota/_/id/9643362/seleccion-mexicana-santiago-gimenez-gol-esperado|title= Santiago Giménez y el gol que soñaba desde niño|website=espn.com.mx|date=8 December 2021}}</ref>

In October 2022, Giménez was named in Mexico's preliminary 31-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], but did not make the final 26, generating controversy.<ref>{{cite web|title=Oficial: Los 5 sacrificados de la Selección Mexicana para Qatar 2022|url=https://www.tvazteca.com/aztecadeportes/sacrificados-seleccion-mexicana-qatar-2022|work=Tvazteca.com|first=Pedro|last=Gálvez|date=14 November 2022|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esto.com.mx/880673-gerardo-martino-sigue-firme-en-dejar-fuera-a-santiago-gimenez-del-mundial-de-qatar-2022/|title=Gerardo Martino sigue firme en dejar fuera a Santiago Giménez del Mundial de Qatar 2022|first=Eduardo|last=Pigeón|date=18 March 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxdeportes.com/seleccion-mexicana/nota/santiago-gimenez-y-las-absurdas-razones-para-no-llevarlo-a-catar-2022|title=Santiago Giménez y las absurdas razones para no llevarlo a Catar 2022|first=F. O. X.|last=Deportes|website=www.foxdeportes.com}}</ref>

On 16 July 2023, Giménez scored the only goal in the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup final|CONCACAF Gold Cup final]] against [[Panama national football team|Panama]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 July 2023 |title=Gimenez's late strike earns Mexico ninth Gold Cup crown |url=https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/article/gimenez-s-late-strike-earns-mexico-ninth-gold-cup-crown/ |access-date=17 July 2023 |website=CONCACAF}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Santiago is the son of footballer [[Christian Giménez (footballer, born 1981)|Christian Giménez]], who also played with Cruz Azul. Born in [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina, Giménez moved to Mexico at the age of three with his father after he was transferred to [[Liga MX|Primera División]] side [[C.D. Veracruz|Veracruz]].<ref name="birthplace"/> His paternal grandfather is from Paraguay<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/chaco-gimenez-apoya-funes-mori-a-mi-me-dijeron-convenenciero-naturalizarme|title='A mí me dijeron convenenciero por amar a México'; Chaco apoya a Funes|first=Editorial|last=Mediotiempo|date=20 September 2025|website=Mediotiempo}}</ref> and he is of Italian and Ukrainian ancestry through his mother's side.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 July 2023 |title='Realmente me siento mexicano': ¿Dónde nació Santiago Giménez y cuál es su nacionalidad? |url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/deportes/2023/07/19/donde-nacio-santiago-gimenez-revela-por-que-juega-con-la-seleccion-mexicana/ |access-date=5 May 2025 |website=El Financiero |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=28 November 2023 |title=Santi Giménez debutó con 15 años con su padre como compañeroi |trans-title=Santi Giménez made his debut at 15 years old with his father as his teammate. |url=https://as.com/futbol/champions/santi-gimenez-debuto-con-15-anos-con-su-padre-como-companero-n/}}</ref> He is a [[Christians|Christian]] and was baptized in January 2019.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Collazo |first1=Jonathan |title=Tri. Santiago Giménez: 'Dios tiene otro camino para mi' |url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/santiago-gimenez-quedar-fuera-qatar-2022-dios-tiene-otro-camino-para-mi |access-date=8 May 2023 |work=Mediotiempo |date=14 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221164924/https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/seleccion-mayor/santiago-gimenez-quedar-fuera-qatar-2022-dios-tiene-otro-camino-para-mi |archive-date=21 February 2023 |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bobadilla |first1=Karina |title=Santi Giménez: De pasar por tres operaciones y temer por su vida a cumplir el sueño europeo |url=https://vamoscruzazul.bolavip.com/noticias/Santi-Gimenez-De-pasar-por-tres-operaciones-y-temer-por-su-vida-a-cumplir-el-sueno-europeo-20220730-0006.html |access-date=8 May 2023 |work=Vamos Azul |date=30 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221164930/https://vamoscruzazul.bolavip.com/noticias/Santi-Gimenez-De-pasar-por-tres-operaciones-y-temer-por-su-vida-a-cumplir-el-sueno-europeo-20220730-0006.html |archive-date=21 February 2023 |language=es-ES}}</ref> Giménez is married to Mexican actress Fernanda Serrano.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Suárez |first1=Marlem |title=¡La beboda! Santiago Giménez se casó con Fernanda Serrano, así fue la ceremonia {{!}} Fotos |trans-title=The baby! Santiago Giménez married Fernanda Serrano, this was the ceremony {{!}} Photos |url=https://www.infobae.com/mexico/2024/05/26/la-beboda-santiago-gimenez-se-caso-con-fernanda-serrano-asi-fue-la-ceremonia-fotos/ |access-date=12 December 2024 |work=Infobae |date=26 May 2024 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

